    "figures": [
      {
        "caption": "A depiction of the~\\AL agentic workflow, focusing on the main components: a primary backbone model to orchestrate calculations and information flow in the cosmology, particle, and nuclear physics domains, as well as interaction with a specialized knowledge base.",
        "filename": "AL-flow_v2.png",
        "key": "946a7aa31625a2e1d307eb40a66647fc",
        "label": "fig:flow",
        "material": "preprint",
        "source": "arxiv",
        "url": "https://inspirehep.net/files/946a7aa31625a2e1d307eb40a66647fc"
      },
      {
        "caption": "Once~\\AL is directed toward a standard~\\CLASS build, it can agentically setup run cards and executions base on a range of cosmology scenarios and microphysics assumptions. These may be steered based on initial dialogue with the backbone agent and consultation of the knowledge base. In this example, we illustrate a set of power spectra (left) generated by~\\AL as well as families of deviations from these defaults based on sterile neutrino scenarios (right).",
        "filename": "sterile_demo_Dell_auto.png",
        "key": "824d352829b338e5d78fc5d215c9142a",
        "label": "fig:cosmo-sterile-nu",
        "material": "preprint",
        "source": "arxiv",
        "url": "https://inspirehep.net/files/824d352829b338e5d78fc5d215c9142a"
      },
      {
        "caption": "Once~\\AL is directed toward a standard~\\CLASS build, it can agentically setup run cards and executions base on a range of cosmology scenarios and microphysics assumptions. These may be steered based on initial dialogue with the backbone agent and consultation of the knowledge base. In this example, we illustrate a set of power spectra (left) generated by~\\AL as well as families of deviations from these defaults based on sterile neutrino scenarios (right).",
        "filename": "sterile_demo_Dell_cross.png",
        "key": "ca2462aa076a063b7b6dae9462aa7391",
        "label": "fig:cosmo-sterile-nu",
        "material": "preprint",
        "source": "arxiv",
        "url": "https://inspirehep.net/files/ca2462aa076a063b7b6dae9462aa7391"
      },
      {
        "caption": "Mirroring the \\CLASS setup, \\AL can also invoke and steer computations relevant for particle-nuclear physics. For instance, these can include the assumption of a definite SM or BSM theory baseline ({\\it i.e.}, corresponding to a particular Lagrangian), from which collider simulations and kinematical matchings to observables relevant to nuclear science might be performed. We illustrate this with a rapidity distribution in $y_{\\ell^+\\ell^-}$ for 13 TeV neutral-current Drell-Yan (left) and corresponding kinematical matchings relevant for DIS observables with modeled detector-smearing effects (right), both produced in automated fashion within~\\AL.",
        "filename": "SM_Z-dilep_rapidity_hist.png",
        "key": "718543975d77b2c9a7383cab090fc398",
        "label": "fig:part-nucl",
        "material": "preprint",
        "source": "arxiv",
        "url": "https://inspirehep.net/files/718543975d77b2c9a7383cab090fc398"
      },
      {
